  </metadata>
  <prompt>Implement click handler on regarding-name link in NarrativeBullet that calls `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo({pageType: 'entityrecord', entityName, entityId}, {target: 2, width: {value: 80, unit: '%'}, height: {value: 80, unit: '%'}})`. On promise rejection (Dataverse 403 or other), show non-blocking Fluent v9 `Toaster` toast: "Cannot open record — you may not have access."</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. Expert in Fluent UI v9 + React hooks + Xrm.WebApi.</role>
  <goal>Click regarding-name link → modal record form opens (80%×80% center). On error (403 or other), non-blocking toast shown — no error overlay or page crash.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>FR-19: Replace existing link behavior with modal navigation + graceful 403 handling. Toaster mount belongs at DailyBriefingApp level (app-scoped notifications); the link click handler in NarrativeBullet calls a callback that fires both navigation and toast on error.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/components/NarrativeBullet.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/DailyBriefingApp.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 only; semantic tokens; dark mode required; use Fluent v9 Toaster primitives</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-024">Preserve useInlineTodoCreate + TODO_REGARDING_CATALOG in Add to To Do</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">R3 PR #451 file overlap — see notes/risks.md R1; run conflict-check before merge</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Preserve R3 deliverables: schema, TTL=604800, read-state, 3 actions (now via overflow menu)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Toast MUST be non-blocking (no error overlay); single Toaster mount at DailyBriefingApp level</constraint>
  </constraints>
