  <steps>
    <step order="1">In DailyBriefingApp.tsx, mount Fluent v9 `Toaster` (single instance at app root); obtain `dispatchToast` via `useToastController`</step>
    <step order="2">Add `handleOpenRecord(entityName, entityId)` to DailyBriefingApp: calls `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo({pageType:'entityrecord', entityName, entityId}, {target:2, width:{value:80,unit:'%'}, height:{value:80,unit:'%'}})`; on `.catch(err)` dispatch toast "Cannot open record — you may not have access."</step>
    <step order="3">Pass `handleOpenRecord` down to NarrativeBullet via ActivityNotesSection</step>
    <step order="4">In NarrativeBullet, wire the regarding-name link's `onClick` to call `handleOpenRecord(entityName, entityId)`; preventDefault on the anchor</step>
    <step order="5">Wire the "Open record" overflow menu item (from task 046) to also call `handleOpenRecord` — single code path for both entry points</step>
    <step order="6">Verify toast uses semantic tokens (ADR-021); dark mode renders correctly; intent='warning' or 'error' as appropriate</step>
    <step order="7">Add Jest tests: link click invokes Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo with correct args; rejected promise dispatches toast; happy path no toast</step>
    <step order="8">Mock Xrm.Navigation in tests; use jest.fn() and Promise.reject for 403 simulation</step>
    <step order="9">Run `npm test`; ensure pass</step>
    <step order="10">Run `npm run build`; verify TypeScript compiles</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md ✅</step>
    <step order="12">Document deviations in notes/</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build/test TypeScript widget</tool>
  </tools>
