  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Click → modal opens for user with Dataverse read access (FR-19 / AC-19a)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Click → toast shown (no error overlay) for user without Dataverse read access (FR-19 / AC-19b)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Toast uses Fluent v9 Toaster + semantic tokens per ADR-021; renders in dark mode</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <ui-tests>
    <test>Click regarding-name link with access → modal opens at 80%×80%; entityName + entityId correct</test>
    <test>Click regarding-name link without access (mock 403) → Toaster shows "Cannot open record — you may not have access."; no error overlay</test>
    <test>Click "Open record" overflow menu item → same navigation path; same 403 handling</test>
    <test>Dark Mode Compliance: Toaster + toast intent color use semantic tokens per ADR-021; no raw hex; contrast meets WCAG AA</test>
    <test>Console Errors: no uncaught promise rejections; 403 case shows toast cleanly with no console error stack</test>
  </ui-tests>
  <notes>Parallel-safe with task 046 because they touch different code surfaces within the same file set (link handler vs overflow callbacks). But sequential under group "none" because both depend on task 045 menu structure and both edit DailyBriefingApp.tsx. R3 PR #451 overlap — run conflict-check. Toaster mount must be at app root (single instance) per Fluent v9 best practice.</notes>
